pickle-testspec-subpage: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-subpage-desc}} Used while creating a link to the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for pickle-style tests.
pickle-testspec-invoke: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-invoke-desc}} Used while invoking the module on the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for pickle-style tests.
pickle-testcase-subpage: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-subpage-desc}} Used while creating a link to the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for testcase-style tests.
pickle-testcase-invoke: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-invoke-desc}} Used while invoking the module on the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for testcase-style tests.
pickle-default-subpage: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-subpage-desc}} Used while creating a link to the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for default tests, that is the catch all.
pickle-default-invoke: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-invoke-desc}} Used while invoking the module on the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for default tests, that is the catch all.
pickle-test-text-good: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|good}} A good result is one where all reported tests were ok.
pickle-test-text-pending: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|pending}} A pending result is one where one or more reported tests were pending.
pickle-test-text-fail: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|failed}} A failed result is one where one or more reported tests were not ok.
pickle-test-text-missing: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|missing}} A missing result is one where the test page could not be found.
pickle-test-text-unknown: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|unknown}} An unknown result is one where the reported tests could not be parsed.
pickle-test-text-todo-good: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|good}} A good result is one where all reported tests marked "todo" were ok.
pickle-test-text-todo-fail: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|failed}} A failed result is one where one or more reported tests marked "todo" were not ok.
pickle-test-text-skip-good: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|good}} A good result is one where all reported tests marked "skip" were ok.
pickle-test-text-skip-fail: {{pickle-gloss}} {{pickle-indicator-desc|failed}} A failed result is one where one or more reported tests marked "skip" were not ok.
pickle-track-log-header: {{pickle-gloss}} Description used on top of Special:log when filtered on this specific log.
pickle-track-log-entry-good: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be good according to the TAP-format.
pickle-track-log-entry-pending: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be pending.
pickle-track-log-entry-todo-good: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be good according to the TAP-format, but the result is also marked as "todo".
pickle-track-log-entry-todo-fail: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be failing according to the TAP-format, but the result is also marked as "todo".
pickle-track-log-entry-skip-good: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be good according to the TAP-format, but the result is also marked as "skip".
pickle-track-log-entry-skip-fail: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be failing according to the TAP-format, but the result is also marked as "skip".
pickle-track-log-entry-fail: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be failing according to the TAP-format.
pickle-track-log-entry-exists: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, but the result is something else than a valid TAP-format.
pickle-track-log-entry-missing: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage does not exists.
pickle-track-log-entry-unknown: {{pickle-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result can't be established in any known way.
pickle-console-title: {{pickle-gloss}} Area used for test reports. Can be empty, but will then have a message about this.
pickle-console-empty: {{pickle-gloss}} Message used to clarify that the output area is initially empty.
pickle-console-cleared: {{pickle-gloss}} Message used to clarify that the output area is cleared.
pickle-console-run: {{pickle-gloss}} Button to initiate a run of a test case. After the completed run the report will be appended to the output area.
pickle-console-clear: {{pickle-gloss}} Button to initiate a clearing of previous test cases. After clearing the output area a message to the effect will be injected.
pickle-report-skip-no-message: {{pickle-gloss}} [delete entry?] Error message for non-existing message keys. Indicates a missing or wrong implementation, possibly on some kind of extension.
pickle-frame-compact-header-all-good: {{pickle-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the compact layout when all contained constituents are good. Initial "ok" must be retained, but can be followed by an explanation.
pickle-frame-compact-header-some-failed: {{pickle-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the compact layout when some contained constituents have failed. Initial "not ok" must be retained, but can be followed by an explanation.
pickle-frame-full-header: {{pickle-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the full layout. Initial hash (#) must be retained.
pickle-frame-vivid-header: {{pickle-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the full layout.
pickle-report-result-compact-is-ok: {{pickle-gloss}} Initial keyword "ok" used for each good test in a TAP-report. It can be adapted by a following localization "ok (something)", but keep the "ok". {{pickle-report-compact}}}
pickle-report-result-compact-is-not-ok: {{pickle-gloss}} Initial keyword "not ok" used for each good test in a TAP-report. It can be adapted by a following localization "not ok (something)", but keep the "not ok". {{pickle-report-compact}}}
pickle-report-result-compact-wrap-skip: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "skip" keyword and the optional string. It can be adapted by a following localization "skip (something)". {{pickle-report-compact}}}
pickle-report-result-compact-wrap-todo: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "todo" keyword and the optional string. It can be freely adapted, but should not contain a hash mark. {{pickle-report-compact}}}
pickle-report-result-compact-wrap-descri: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the description optional string. {{pickle-report-compact}}}
pickle-report-result-compact-wrap-line: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the collected lines. {{pickle-report-compact}}}

pickle-report-result-full-wrap-skip: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "skip" keyword and the optional string. It can be adapted by a following localization "skip (something)". {{pickle-report-full}}}
pickle-report-result-full-wrap-todo: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "todo" keyword and the optional string. It can be freely adapted, but should not contain a hash mark. {{pickle-report-full}}}
pickle-report-result-full-wrap-descripti: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the description optional string. {{pickle-report-full}}}
pickle-report-result-full-wrap-line: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the collected lines. {{pickle-report-full}}}
pickle-report-result-vivid-is-ok: {{pickle-gloss}} Initial keyword "ok" used for each good test in a TAP-report. It can be adapted by a following localization "ok (something)", but keep the "ok". {{pickle-report-vivid}}

pickle-report-result-vivid-wrap-todo: {{pickle-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "todo" keyword and the optional string. It can be freely adapted, but should not contain a hash mark. {{pickle-report-vivid}}
